The Great Irish Bake Off - Series 3, Episode 1




Desserts

Anna Nolan presents the third run of the baking challenge, with food writer Lilly Higgins joining the show alongside returning judge Paul Kelly. In the first stage, the 12 contestants tackle desserts, with each trying to create a dish inspired by a memorable moment. They also face their first technical challenge, as Paul sets them to work on exotic cheesecakes.




Original Air Date: 25-Oct-2015
